And you can't really read the name of the
app from here.

00:09:56.990 --> 00:10:00.290
It fades into the background, the contrast
isn't really high enough, and the words are

00:10:00.290 --> 00:10:01.290
too small.

00:10:01.290 --> 00:10:06.230
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: No, all I see is X with maybe
an E and something that's either an R or an

00:10:06.230 --> 00:10:07.850
X.
&gt;&gt; MEIER: Next to it, yeah.

00:10:07.850 --> 00:10:08.850
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: Yeah.

00:10:08.850 --> 00:10:09.850
&gt;&gt; MEIER: Who can say?

00:10:09.850 --> 00:10:13.850
So that, you know, they've got the table stakes
here, they've got the ability to be featured

00:10:13.850 --> 00:10:17.180
or promoted in Google Play by having a feature
graphic which is really important...

00:10:17.180 --> 00:10:18.180
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: Uh-hmm.

00:10:18.180 --> 00:10:20.150
&gt;&gt; MEIER: ...but they haven't taken advantage
of it.

00:10:20.150 --> 00:10:24.190
We've seen just recently people blogging,
talking about the fact that just having a

00:10:24.190 --> 00:10:28.460
better feature graphic can have significant
impact and your downloads, should you be fortunate

00:10:28.460 --> 00:10:29.460
enough to be promoted.

00:10:29.460 --> 00:10:30.460
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: Exactly.

00:10:30.460 --> 00:10:33.510
I can--I can guarantee that for this one they
wouldn't run it.

00:10:33.510 --> 00:10:38.080
They--this would get kicked back to the developer
just because it's eligible at those--at those

00:10:38.080 --> 00:10:39.080
dimensions.

00:10:39.080 --> 00:10:40.080
&gt;&gt; MEIER: Absolutely.

00:10:40.080 --> 00:10:42.260
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: So, what--why don't you show
