00:40:57.519 --> 00:41:01.710
testimonial saying how the wonderful the app
is on an iPhone.

00:41:01.710 --> 00:41:04.179
Now that's a not entirely good practice.

00:41:04.179 --> 00:41:05.200
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: You know what--yeah.

00:41:05.200 --> 00:41:09.480
I mean it--I don't--I don't think it bothers
us but it bothers our merchandising team.

00:41:09.480 --> 00:41:10.480
&gt;&gt; MEIER: Yeah.

00:41:10.480 --> 00:41:11.480
Good for...

00:41:11.480 --> 00:41:12.480
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: Spectacularly.

00:41:12.480 --> 00:41:14.290
&gt;&gt; MEIER: So, if you're building an app like
this and you want to be featured and frankly

00:41:14.290 --> 00:41:15.290
who doesn't?

00:41:15.290 --> 00:41:16.989
You may want to consider things like that.

00:41:16.989 --> 00:41:20.809
There's someone on Google Play and merchandising
team who's going to look at these apps and

00:41:20.809 --> 00:41:23.710
if doesn't have a feature graphic they're
going to pass it by.

00:41:23.710 --> 00:41:28.459
If it's cooling out competitors it probably
going to think twice as well.

00:41:28.459 --> 00:41:33.160
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: So, prescriptions for MX Player
are considerably shorter because we both love

00:41:33.160 --> 00:41:34.160
the app.

00:41:34.160 --> 00:41:35.160
&gt;&gt; MEIER: It was a nice app, yeah.

00:41:35.160 --> 00:41:38.059
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: But we'd really like to see a
better ActionBar.

00:41:38.059 --> 00:41:39.059
&gt;&gt; MEIER: Yeah.

00:41:39.059 --> 00:41:40.059
It seems like such an easy win.

00:41:40.059 --> 00:41:43.039
You know, they're already using all of the
native Android 4.0 stuff.

00:41:43.039 --> 00:41:45.650
They've got an ActionBar or something very
much like it in the view.

00:41:45.650 --> 00:41:49.880
Putting it in the browser as well and give
us that experience that we used to.

00:41:49.880 --> 00:41:50.880
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: Absolutely.

00:41:50.880 --> 00:41:54.829
But the video playback I think in general
is really--was really great.

00:41:54.829 --> 00:42:00.529
The only thing that wasn't jarring was that
I would go from the video playback which is

00:42:00.529 --> 00:42:08.219
a dark theme and, you know, usually a high
contrast experience with the videos that I

00:42:08.219 --> 00:42:09.219
watched.

00:42:09.219 --> 00:42:14.400
And then I would be flopped directly into
this light themed browser and especially at

00:42:14.400 --> 00:42:18.519
night, you know, if I'm watching videos in
bed or whatever that was a little bit jarring.

00:42:18.519 --> 00:42:19.519
&gt;&gt; MEIER: Yes.

00:42:19.519 --> 00:42:22.950
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: I feel like maybe a dark theme
is a better choice for some of these apps.

00:42:22.950 --> 00:42:24.790
&gt;&gt; MEIER: Yeah, seems like it would make sense.

00:42:24.790 --> 00:42:27.039
I did want to call out as well with MX Player.

00:42:27.039 --> 00:42:30.529
One of the things that they do really well
is feasibility to the play pretty much anything

00:42:30.529 --> 00:42:31.529
we throw at it.

00:42:31.529 --> 00:42:33.349
We throw some pretty upscale media codecs
at it.

00:42:33.349 --> 00:42:38.829
I was able to decode everything if not always
at full speed at least it was able to figure

00:42:38.829 --> 00:42:39.910
it out which is really impressive.

00:42:39.910 --> 00:42:40.910
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: That's absolutely true.

00:42:40.910 --> 00:42:43.820
I remember we throw a quick time animation...

00:42:43.820 --> 00:42:44.820
&gt;&gt; MEIER: Yes.

00:42:44.820 --> 00:42:45.839
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: ...play--video at it.

00:42:45.839 --> 00:42:46.839
&gt;&gt; MEIER: And it didn't choke.

00:42:46.839 --> 00:42:47.839
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: No.

00:42:47.839 --> 00:42:48.839
&gt;&gt; MEIER: Which surprised me.

00:42:48.839 --> 00:42:51.119
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: It played very slowly but then
again so did my [INDISTINCT]

00:42:51.119 --> 00:42:52.489
&gt;&gt; MEIER: Exactly right.

00:42:52.489 --> 00:42:56.180
It also passed the test--it was the only app
that we looked at that was able to play back

00:42:56.180 --> 00:42:59.069
media which we plug into the device in any
ways.

00:42:59.069 --> 00:43:04.479
So, whether that was native on the device,
via SD card or even by via USB key for which

00:43:04.479 --> 00:43:09.920
I managed to dig out of a skeleton--well,
not skeleton but a cobweb string corner.

00:43:09.920 --> 00:43:11.460
I was still able to do that.

00:43:11.460 --> 00:43:12.539
So, that's--that was impressive.

00:43:12.539 --> 00:43:16.089
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: A DICE Player did a lot of things
right.

00:43:16.089 --> 00:43:18.999
Most importantly I think it got its defaults
right.

00:43:18.999 --> 00:43:19.999
&gt;&gt; MEIER: Yes.

00:43:19.999 --> 00:43:22.180
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: If a video could be hardware
accelerated it was.

00:43:22.180 --> 00:43:25.430
And I think you were pointing out if a video
is very small.

00:43:25.430 --> 00:43:27.109
&gt;&gt; MEIER: It automatically full screened it.

00:43:27.109 --> 00:43:28.650
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: Which none of the other players
did.

00:43:28.650 --> 00:43:29.650
I was surprised.

00:43:29.650 --> 00:43:30.650
&gt;&gt; MEIER: Yeah.

00:43:30.650 --> 00:43:31.650
And you can argue either way.

00:43:31.650 --> 00:43:35.349
You can say that they should be showing it
to you in its native resolution first and

00:43:35.349 --> 00:43:39.400
foremost but really if you're looking at these
apps--at this--at these videos I should say

00:43:39.400 --> 00:43:42.670
on a tablet or on a phone chances are you
just want it to be full screened.

00:43:42.670 --> 00:43:45.440
You just want to enjoy it in its immersive
experience as possible.

00:43:45.440 --> 00:43:48.130
So, it kind of makes sense to default that
way.

00:43:48.130 --> 00:43:51.400
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: So, really there--we just had
some nit.

00:43:51.400 --> 00:43:57.950
We really liked the DICE Player playback engine
and the way that it handles defaults correctly

00:43:57.950 --> 00:44:01.399
but we really hated the way that it hid the
notification bar.

00:44:01.399 --> 00:44:02.399
&gt;&gt; MEIER: Yes.

00:44:02.399 --> 00:44:06.910
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: And this is nit picky but we
felt like the ActionBar could use a little

00:44:06.910 --> 00:44:08.420
bit of work when you...

00:44:08.420 --> 00:44:09.420
&gt;&gt; MEIER: Yeah.

00:44:09.420 --> 00:44:12.220
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: ...hit the back button it popped
a confirm exit dialogue.

00:44:12.220 --> 00:44:13.220
&gt;&gt; MEIER: Yeah.

00:44:13.220 --> 00:44:14.220
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: ...which I don't even know why
you do.

00:44:14.220 --> 00:44:15.220
&gt;&gt; MEIER: No.

00:44:15.220 --> 00:44:19.319
Exactly, I mean this confirm to exit is one
of my pet peeves along with the exit buttons

00:44:19.319 --> 00:44:20.700
and exit menu items.

00:44:20.700 --> 00:44:22.019
There really isn't need for it.

00:44:22.019 --> 00:44:26.430
There's no need to confirm to exit just make
sure that there is no status loss when they

00:44:26.430 --> 00:44:27.430
exit.

00:44:27.430 --> 00:44:31.099
You know, you get the on pause, you get the
on stop, record, shared preferences it says

00:44:31.099 --> 00:44:35.049
what movie they're watching, what the current
playback position is and then if the app gets

00:44:35.049 --> 00:44:37.230
killed while you're in the background well
that's fine.

00:44:37.230 --> 00:44:39.319
When you load up, load it all up full.

00:44:39.319 --> 00:44:44.229
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: You know I worked with a lot
of video games that were really, really concerned

00:44:44.229 --> 00:44:49.079
about what happens when you exit but that's
because they're building this gigantic OpenGL

00:44:49.079 --> 00:44:50.119
structures...

00:44:50.119 --> 00:44:51.119
&gt;&gt; MEIER: Yeah.

00:44:51.119 --> 00:44:54.719
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: ...and they're loading lots of
texture but with this really you're recording

00:44:54.719 --> 00:45:01.049
where you're at in the video and maybe, you
know, zoom level and volume and brightness

00:45:01.049 --> 00:45:02.049
and...

00:45:02.049 --> 00:45:03.049
&gt;&gt; MEIER: Yeah.

00:45:03.049 --> 00:45:06.369
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: ...a few other settings that's
it because resurrecting the video playback

00:45:06.369 --> 00:45:10.459
engine on Android is a very, very quick task.

00:45:10.459 --> 00:45:11.459
&gt;&gt; MEIER: Absolutely.

00:45:11.459 --> 00:45:13.930
They're hardly reticulating any [INDISTINCT]
&gt;&gt; NI-LEWIS: Exactly.

00:45:13.930 --> 00:45:16.839
So, get rid of that.

00:45:16.839 --> 00:45:19.619
Get rid of the customs status bar during the
playback.

00:45:19.619 --> 00:45:23.330
We really rather just see the normal notification
bar and...

00:45:23.330 --> 00:45:26.509
&gt;&gt; MEIER: And then that it is--because it
